when my repository is brand new:
git init  -- to initialice my repository in my folder
git add .
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M master
git remote add origin https://github.com/charommolina/My-CSS.git
git push -u origin master


when i want to update my repository:
git status -- it checks to see what new files or new changes are in your project
git add . -- adds all the files in red
git status
git commit -m "comment" -- this prepares to send the files over to your git repository with a message
git push - sends your new updates to the repository
